# Conventional Commit Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, chore, test, refactor, perf, ci
# Scope: connector, rules, audit, storage, iOS, Android, etc.
# Description: imperative, lowercase, no period
#
# Example:
#   feat(connector-canvas): handle 429 with Retry-After backoff
#
# Body (optional): explain what and why, not how.
#
# Footer: reference issues and DCO sign-off.
#   Closes #123
#   Traces to: FR-CONN-003
#   Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
#
# To use: git config commit.template .gitmessage

